  "issues": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "id": "I_kwDOLPL1Dc5-isOK",
      "title": "Overall design",
      "url": "https://github.com/boucadair/draft-cwbgp-energy-saving-management/issues/1",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "boucadair",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Please find attached some quick comments/inputs about the draft. I embedded some comments directly in the file, with items that I think are easy to fix: use identities rather than enumeration, 64 instead of 32, gauge, etc.\r\n\r\nNow for the design, I\u2019m not comfortable to graft the energy optimization directly into the inventory. I suggest to split the design into two parts: energy saving capabilities that can be stored in an inventory and another set of features to tweak those while taking into account topology matters",
      "createdAt": "2024-02-07T13:19:56Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-02-07T13:19:56Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
